item.title: [WIP] Mustang
item.dc:creator: @SomethingToHide STH
item.description:
@SomethingToHide wrote:

Haha. As Chris reminded me about Maxwell…

I had started making some MXM Materials the other day waiting for it to render.
So today I picked that up again, and finished them all.

Then I cleaned the entire model. Collapsed everything. Deleted everything I didn’t need. Reorganized it and renamed everything efficiently. Exported, and opened in Maxwell.

I think this project is about to be done. With the crits from that last image, I didn’t really do anything. Mainly because the grill artifact is shader-based, the geometry is fine. And I like the way the sides are. And that light is on, the glare just didn’t show up cause of the angle =/

So. In Maxwell, I finished everything up. Started rendering. It’s been going for about 30 minutes now. I came back here to see what you said, and saw my latest picture. This final render makes that look like a fucking joke. Seriously. I almost shit myself over how proud I am over what I’ve acheived.

So. Either I’m going to post in a few minutes and go shopping and let you guys crit it.
Or, go shopping and let it finish out the artifacts.
Or, post it now for crits, let it render overnight for a higher quality render and use that as the final.

What should I do?

EDIT: Doing the latter. Tell me everything you have to say now. I’m about to start a final image.

Read full topic
